    • Constructor Detail

      • RationalNumber

        public RationalNumber(int numerator,
                      int denominator)
               throws IllegalArgumentException
        This is the constructor for the RationalNumber. This creates a number in the format: num⁄den where num is the numerator and den is the denominator.
        Parameters:
        numerator - the numerator of the fraction
        denominator - the denominator of the fraction. This may not be 0.
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException - thrown is 0 is passed as the denominator
